        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Firefox Version 32'); ?>
        <p><strong>Firefox 32</strong> was released on 2 September 2014. It shows off <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HTTP', 'IPA'); ?> caching improvements, adds HiDPI/Retina support in the Developer Tools UI and widens <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HTML5', 'WD'); ?> support, among other things. Firefox 32.0.1 was released for mobile only on 10 September fixing the link tap selection that is offset on some <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Android', 'OS'); ?> devices; and for desktop two days later, fixing stability issues. Firefox 32.0.2 was released for desktop only on 18 September fixing the corrupt installations causing Firefox to crash on update. Firefox 32.0.3 was released for desktop and Android on 24 September fixing a security vulnerability.</p>
